er image? Or is there a how-to somewhere?", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>We are trying to build the docker solution images based on our solution that is stored on our local file system. Thanks to the hints in issue <a href=\"#!/osrf/subt/issues/154/systemsetupdockerinstall-should-contain\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"SystemSetupDockerInstall should contain the docker installation step\" class=\"ap-connect-link\"><s>#154</s></a> we got a better understanding and an instruction. But we have our solution in a local file system and not in an external repository as the dockerfile on subt_seed uses. </p>\n<p>So how can we copy the src-Folder from our local file system into the docker image? Or is there a how-to somewhere?</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "assignee": {"display_name": "Alfredo Bencomo", "uuid": "{84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B84891a71-dff2-4b97-8891-9446c16e6f89%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/5cf75629ff02b50ea27b2817/82be1d48-d490-4d7b-8ddb-a8093b9417a6/128"}}, "nickname": "bencomo", "type": "user", "account_id": "5cf75629ff02b50ea27b2817"}, "state": "closed", "version": null, "edited_on": null, "created_on": "2019-09-29T15:03:28.629446+00:00", "milestone": null, "updated_on": "2019-10-31T05:47:20.255284+00:00", "type": "issue", "id": 210}